TY  - JOUR
T1  - State Capacity, Conflict, and Development
AU  - Besley, Timothy
AU  - Persson, Torsten
Y1  - 2010/01/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA8073
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1
EP  - 34
VL  - 78
IS  - 1
KW  - State building
KW  - civil war
KW  - weak states
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA8073
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - The absence of state capacities to raise revenue and to support markets is a key factor in explaining the persistence of weak states. This paper reports on an ongoing project to investigate the incentive to invest in such capacities. The paper sets out a simple analytical structure in which state capacities are modeled as forward looking investments by government. The approach highlights some determinants of state building including the risk of external or internal conflict, the degree of political instability, and dependence on natural resources. Throughout, we link these state capacity investments to patterns of development and growth.
ER  - 

