TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Model of Delegated Project Choice
AU  - Armstrong, Mark
AU  - Vickers, John
Y1  - 2010/01/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA7965
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 213
EP  - 244
VL  - 78
IS  - 1
KW  - Delegation
KW  - principal–agent
KW  - rules
KW  - merger policy
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA7965
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We present a model in which a principal delegates the choice of project to an agent with different preferences. The principal determines the set of projects from which the agent may choose. The principal can verify the characteristics of the project chosen by the agent, but does not know which other projects were available to the agent. We consider situations where the collection of available projects is exogenous to the agent but uncertain, where the agent must invest effort to discover a project, where the principal can pay the agent to choose a desirable project, and where the principal can adopt more complex schemes than simple permission sets.
ER  - 

