TY  - JOUR
T1  - Evaluating Marginal Policy Changes and the Average Effect of Treatment for Individuals at the Margin
AU  - Carneiro, Pedro
AU  - Heckman, James J.
AU  - Vytlacil, Edward
Y1  - 2010/01/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA7089
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 377
EP  - 394
VL  - 78
IS  - 1
KW  - Marginal treatment effect
KW  - effects of marginal policy changes
KW  - marginal policy relevant treatment effect
KW  - average marginal treatment effect
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA7089
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - This paper develops methods for evaluating marginal policy changes. We characterize how the effects of marginal policy changes depend on the direction of the policy change, and show that marginal policy effects are fundamentally easier to identify and to estimate than conventional treatment parameters. We develop the connection between marginal policy effects and the average effect of treatment for persons on the margin of indifference between participation in treatment and nonparticipation, and use this connection to analyze both parameters. We apply our analysis to estimate the effect of marginal changes in tuition on the return to going to college.
ER  - 

